title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
Hello, I have a clean plate with no oxidation. Green Magsafe LED, then orange. But it doesn't. Some measurements.

PPBUS_G3H 12,5v
PP3V42_G3H. 3.4v
PP3v42_G3H 3.4v
PM_RSMRST_L 3v
SMC_ONOFF_L 3,37v
PP3V3_S5 3.3V
PP3V3_SUS 3.3V
PP5V_S5 5v
PM_BATLOW_L 3.3V
SMC_ADAPTER_EN 3.3V
PM_PWRBTN_L 3.4V
PM_RSMRST_L 3V
SMC_PM_G2_EN. - 3.4V
RTC_RESET_L. - 3.26V
PPVRTC_G3H - 3,3V
PCH_SRTCRST_L 3.26V
ALL_SYS_PWRGD 0V

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message: Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check for drop pulse at PM_PWRBTN_L, at same time.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
Hi!

PM_PWRBTN_L pulses to 0.33 when I trigger SMC_ONOFF_L

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message: Check for pulse at both PM_SLP_S4/3_L; when trigger SMC_ONOFF_L.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
Pulses change when I press SMC_ONOFF.

PM_SLP_S4 - 0.33, 0.75
PM_SLP_S4 - 0.33, 0.75, 1.5v

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
You should note a pulse on the big coils too.
Also test on pins 7 & 3 of U1950.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
On the U1950, pin 3 has no pulse, on 7 it has a 0.15 pulse.

The board turned on twice when I was checking the coils. The ones next to the CPU (L7320, L7310, pulse 0.24v).

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
Check for pulse at pin 5 of U1950.

BTW, trigger SMC_ONOFF_L repeatedly, to catch high pulse level...

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message: Pin 5 pulses of: 0.5, 1.2v and sometimes the board turns on, gets 3.3.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
So the board stays on sometime?

Pin 3 of U1950 should pulse at the same time with pin 5.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
When I activate the SMC_ONOFF several times, sometimes it turns on and it works. But if it turns off, it doesn't come back.

Before, testing pin 3, it had no pulse. But the board never turned on either.

I now have a pulse on pins 3 and 5.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
Try with another original 60/85W Magsafe 2 charger.
Also try with known good battery connected.

Test if turns on in SMC bypass, or safe mode.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
Tested with another charger and battery. Nothing!

SMC bypass, nothing. Cooler turns and stops fast.

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message: If you press power button 1-2s, instead of short press, still doesn't turn on?

title: 820-3476 - Orange LED, but no power
message:
nothing.

No longer works on SMC_ONOFF. I tried it a few times and it didn't work.

Customer has urgency. I'll return it. Thank you so much for your help ever!
